OL,4,CReligious groups in UK failing children
OL,5,Cover sex abuse, report says
OL,6, There are "shocking failings" and
OL,7, "blatant hypocrisy" in the way major UK
OL,8, religious groups handle child sex abuse
OL,9, allegations, an inquiry has found.
OL,11,FThe Independent Inquiry into Child
OL,12,FSexual Abuse (IICSA) said some
OL,13,Freligious organisations in England and
OL,14,FWales were "morally failing" children.
OL,16,FIt examined evidence from 38 groups,
OL,17,Fincluding sects from Christianity,
OL,18,FOrthodox Judaism and Islam.
OL,20,FLeaders discouraged reporting abuse to
OL,21,Fprotect reputations, the report found.
